	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well obviously some people dont know how to calculate haste. 100% haste on an item HALVES the delay of the weapon, it does not reduce the dly to 0.&nbsp;&nbsp;I know 100% haste is unattainable, but ill use it as an example.  A lammy with 100% haste has a delay of 9.5, which i know is also unattainable.  A wurm with 100% haste is 20 dly.  50% haste reduces dly of a weapon by 1/4, and so on. THAT is how haste really works, trust me, it does not reduce the dly by the % of haste a spell/item gives.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
